'''win32-loader''' is a component of the [[Debian Installer]] that runs on [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] and has the ability to load the actual installer either from the network (as in the version used in [http://goodbye-microsoft.com/ goodbye-microsoft.com]) or from [[CD-ROM]] media (as in the version included in [[Debian#Releases|lenny]] CD images).
win32-loader was born as an independent project, for which only the network version was available. Later the code would go through a long review and polishing process to become part of the official [[Debian]] distribution.
